Welcome to Murakami! Relax in a spacious traditional Japanese tatami room! This will be your private room during your stay :)
We have an entire building devoted to hosting our guests. You will be sharing the facilities in our guesthouse with 5 other rooms.

The booking includes 2 meals: a Japanese breakfast and a luxurious seafood course (Funamori) on the night of your arrival! If you would rather not have raw fish, we can prepare it cooked :) Also, if you prefer beef, there is also the Wakasa Beef meal plan for an extra 2,500JPY/person
Your host, Mr. Murakami will take you on a 1 hour boat tour around the coast to show you his beautiful hometown. You will not be able to fish from the boat, but you can enjoy the spectacular view.
Mr. Murakami can take you on a boat tour around the bay!
Mr. Murakami can take you out fishing on a dock. (You cannot fish off the boat, though).
This is your host, Mr & Mrs Murakami. They will take great care of you during your stay :)
There is a stunning beach within 5 minutes walking distance from Murakami where you can go swimming!
Your dinner will consist of fresh seafood caught on the same day by local fishermen, if not your host himself.
Depending on the season, you will be able to try out all kinds of seafood.
There are multiple bathrooms located in different parts the building.
You can also use the washing machine to wash your clothes.
All of our toilets are modern and clean.
We provide basic amenities such as toothbrushes, hand soap, and hair dryer in each bathroom.
When this red banner is hung up, the bath is only available for women.
When it's the men's turn, you will see the blue banner.
This is the changing area where you can put your clothes.
There are also a few sinks in the changing area.
In Japan, it is customary to wash your body first by the showers and then enter the hot bath once you are clean.
The dining area is in a separate building. Both dinner and breakfast will take place here.
There is a common area in the guesthouse, where you can talk with other guests and enjoy a game of Go.
Two vending machines are located at the entrance of the guesthouse where you can easily get soft drinks and alcoholic beverages.
We provide air conditioners in each room with both heating and cooling functions.
This is the view of the Fishermen's village from the sea.
As long as the weather permits, you will be able to enjoy 1 hour at sea with your host, Mr. Murakami.
He will show you all the fishing spots around the bay. You cannot fish from the boat, but you can do dock and pier fishing.
Here are some guests enjoying fishing off of the dock!
Here are some guests who stayed with us enjoying the boat tour!
If you walk 5 minutes along the coast, you will be able to reach a lovely beach area where you can bathe in the ocean.
The water is spotless and barely any people are here, so you are likely to have the whole beach to yourself ;)
There is free parking for all guests staying at Murakami.
When you have time, a stroll around the village will give you great insight on how the villagers here live. Their lifestyle has remained mostly unchanged for hundreds of years.
Locals collect seaweed and hang them under the sun to get dried seaweed.
Please feel free to drop us a message if you want to find out more about staying at Murakami. You are welcome any time!

바다만큼은 아니지만 테라스도 넓어서 3~4명은 편히 불편함없이 이용가능하세요

Odra river- slow and fast, high and low, constantly on the move. Only by looking at it, it will calm you down and remind you that everything flows. Floating house with its mirror-spaceship-design will make you feel comfortable while enjoying the flow
All amenities at the house including comfortable bed, espresso machine, amazonian hummock, large terrace and many many more would make every day at the house unforgettable.

Not only design and amenities - but the sunsets and sun rises at that spot would make every evening and every morning a spectacle you would be remembering the rest of your life. Even when it rains or snows the river is magical!

Here it is, the lovely and beautiful Floating House - my prototype of prototypes - moored in a small and quiet port of 1000 year old town of Bytom Odrzański in far-west Poland, with a direct view on a natural bank of Odra river.
Inside, queen bed (160x200) comes miraculously out of the wall - with 2 night lamps and a comfortable mattress - what else do you need to sleep well?
And the amazonian Hummock - you have (until now at least) NO IDEA how much of a pleasure is to hang in it on a floating house. It's about time to try!
Comfortable Bedroom area and a view over the rest of the house - small Kitchen, folded hummock and table, bunkbed area and entry door.
Have a good look at the interior - it's unique and convenient. Consists of Kitchen area, Bedroom as well as Living room area and Bathroom
Have a good look at exterior too! We thought of in when designing the garden furniture for this large terrace comfortable to chill, wine and dine!
We thought you will like good coffee, so we equipped the house with a proper espresso machine for you to enjoy the terrace even more! :)
We also thought of providing you a fast wi-fi connection (on request) along with a remote desk space which can also serve as dining table
And Bathroom - it's so nice, the rain shower, you will resist leaving it as it's so so pleasurable!! But hey, remember to save water, it's limited to some 3000 liter only :)
Bathroom and toilet - isn't it lovely?
Lovely Bathroom with as much toilet paper as you will use in a month, haha!!
This is the view you see when opening the door to the house. Note the bunk bed on the left, which can comfortably sleep 2 adults!
That is the bunkbed closed. It can comfortably sleep 2 adults and in case needed you will get a full bedding for them ready at your arrival!
And that is the bunkbed open. We just hope you are not afraid of heights ;)
The art of a comfortable sleep is what we mastered for 5 years of hosting. Note the view and the art on walls :)
We will leave everything for you to enjoy a healthy breakfast - possible on request upon fee every morning delivered at your door or simply do-it-yourself in this fully equipped Kitchen!
After pulling up the bed, within a minute you can build a comfortable, turkish-style couch, hard pillows and a coffee table! Isn't it nice?
And the amazonian Hummock - you have (until now at least) NO IDEA how much of a pleasure is to hang in it on a floating house. It's about time to try!

Mirror walls both inside and especially outside the house make it disappear within the landscape it is moored. And along with it disappear all your trouble when you get used to floating - trust me - you will not like to leave the place!

Last but not least, the house has a lovely terrace, which you can normally enjoy during the summer with a view like no other where an evening adoration of a river sunset can become your daily routine!
So how do you like what you have seen so far? If you like it already, I guarantee you will love it when staying on it. Don't hesitate, BOOK!
Yes yes, BOOK IT and enjoy the magic of living on the water!
